<p><strong>John Scott House Rehabilitation &amp; Nursing Center &bull;</strong> in Braintree is a 138-bed skilled nursing center, providing short-term rehabilitation and long-term care. John Scott House is the first skilled nursing center established by the Welch Family. With a celebrated <a href="http://www.welchhrg.com/welch-healthcare-retirement-group/history">history of over 65 years</a>, John Scott House offers residents and their families the best of both worlds - a center rich in tradition and quality medical, nursing and rehabilitative care.</p>  <p>John Scott House is conveniently located within a residential community less than a mile from Route 3, off Exit 17. The center is accredited by <a href="http://www.jointcommission.org/" target="_blank">The Joint Commission</a> and is Medicaid/Medicare Certified and accepts coverage from many private insurers.</p>  <p style="margin-left: 40px;">&bull; <a href="/choosing-a-nursing-home">Click here for Frequently Asked Questions about Skilled Nursing</a></p>  <p style="margin-left: 40px;">&bull; <span style="color:#3399cc;">Click here for our Rehabilitation Brochure</span></p> 